          <history>
            <origin>
              <p>Components produced at different times and by different artists; probably compiled as an album in the 19th century. Two calligraphic works are signed and dated: 1) Ibn Muḥammad Riz̤ā Muḥammad, dated 1128 AH [1716 CE] (f. 9r) and 2) Ḥājī Muḥammad Ḥasanī, dated 1069 AH [1658 CE] (f. 11r). A third work is signed [Ḥus]ayn al-Tabrīzī (f. 8v).</p>
              <origDate>1650-1750?</origDate>
              <origPlace>Iran?</origPlace>
            </origin>
            <provenance>Purchased for Columbia with funds donated by J. Dyneley Prince, James Speyer and Jacob H. Schiff; accessioned 1905 (bookplate inside front cover).</provenance>
            <provenance>Formerly owned by Carl Reinhardt; purchased from his estate.</provenance>
          </history>
